<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
gwymodule-tool

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Tool modules

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
Tool modules implement interactive tools allowing users to select parts from
or otherwise `draw' directly on the data windows. The tool interface consists
of a single function <link linkend="GwyToolUseFunc">GwyToolUseFunc</link>
called when a tool is selected for a data window (or un-selected, like when
another tool is selected or the data window is removed), they can be however
quite tricky. You are encouraged to use the
<link linkend="libgwyapp-unitool">GwyUnitool</link> helper to implement your
tool modules.
</para>

<!-- ##### SECTION See_Also ##### -->
<para>
<link linkend="libgwyapp-unitool">GwyUnitool</link>, a tool template
implementing the common functionality of tools.
</para>

